{
  "local_port": 47974,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best restaurants to try when visiting Hubbali, Karnataka, India? What should you try while you're there?",
  "response": "**Hubli (Hubballi), Karnataka**, is a vibrant city known for its diverse culinary scene that blends traditional Karnataka flavors with contemporary cuisine. Whether you're a fan of spicy South Indian dishes, North Indian delicacies, or international flavors, Hubli has something to offer. Here are some of the best restaurants to try and must-try dishes while you're there:\n\n### **Top Restaurants in Hubli**\n\n1. **Cafe Thulp**\n   - **Cuisine:** Multi-cuisine (South Indian, North Indian, Chinese)\n   - **Highlights:** Popular for its relaxed ambiance and a wide variety of dishes. Great for breakfast, lunch, and dinner.\n   - **Must-Try:** Their masala dosa and thali meals.\n\n2. **Woodlands Restaurant**\n   - **Cuisine:** South Indian and North Indian\n   - **Highlights:** Known for its hygienic environment and delicious traditional dishes.\n   - **Must-Try:** Rava dosa, biryanis, and their selection of vegetarian thalis.\n\n3. **Kamat Hotel**\n   - **Cuisine:** Traditional Karnataka and South Indian\n   - **Highlights:** Part of a well-known chain, Kamat offers authentic regional flavors in a comfortable setting.\n   - **Must-Try:** Bisi Bele Bath, Ragi Mudde, and filter coffee.\n\n4. **Sukh Sagar**\n   - **Cuisine:** Vegetarian, primarily South Indian\n   - **Highlights:** Ideal for vegetarians, offering a variety of dosas, idlis, and thalis.\n   - **Must-Try:** Paneer masala dosa and the assorted thali.\n\n5. **Abhi's Corner**\n   - **Cuisine:** Cafe & Fast Food\n   - **Highlights:** A trendy spot loved for its quick bites, desserts, and beverages.\n   - **Must-Try:** Sandwiches, burgers, and their signature shakes.\n\n6. **The Urban Tadka**\n   - **Cuisine:** North Indian, Chinese, and Continental\n   - **Highlights:** Stylish interiors with a diverse menu catering to varied tastes.\n   - **Must-Try:** Butter chicken, paneer tikka, and spring rolls.\n\n7. **Barbeque Nation**\n   - **Cuisine:** Barbecue, North Indian, and Multi-cuisine\n   - **Highlights:** Offers an all-you-can-eat buffet with live grills on the table, perfect for group dining.\n   - **Must-Try:** Their barbecue starters and wide array of curries.\n\n8. **Jaycees Bakery & Sweets**\n   - **Cuisine:** Bakery, Indian Sweets, and Snacks\n   - **Highlights:** Perfect for enjoying freshly baked goods and traditional Indian sweets.\n   - **Must-Try:** Samosas, pastries, and Mysore pak.\n\n### **Must-Try Dishes in Hubli**\n\nWhile enjoying the diverse restaurant offerings, make sure to try these local and regional specialties:\n\n1. **Bisi Bele Bath**\n   - A hearty one-pot dish made with rice, lentils, vegetables, and a special spice mix.\n\n2. **Dosa Varieties**\n   - From the classic masala dosa to rava dosa and set dosa, these fermented crepes are a South Indian staple.\n\n3. **Ragi Mudde**\n   - Finger millet balls served with spicy sambar or curry, a traditional Karnataka meal.\n\n4. **Vada Pav**\n   - A popular street food consisting of a spicy potato fritter sandwiched between bread, often enjoyed with chutneys.\n\n5. **Filter Coffee**\n   - Strong and aromatic South Indian coffee served with milk and sugar, perfect to accompany any meal.\n\n6. **Mysore Pak**\n   - A rich, sweet dessert made from gram flour, ghee, and sugar, originating from nearby Mysore but widely enjoyed in Hubli.\n\n7. **Jowar Rotti**\n   - Sorghum flatbreads often served with spicy curries or chutneys.\n\n8. **Paneer Tikka & Butter Chicken**\n   - For those who enjoy North Indian cuisine, these dishes are flavorful and widely available in multi-cuisine restaurants.\n\n### **Local Tips**\n\n- **Street Food:** Don't miss out on trying local street foods like pani puri, pani bhaji, and egg rolls available at various stalls around the city.\n  \n- **Thali Meals:** Opt for a traditional Karnataka thali to sample a variety of dishes in one meal, giving you a comprehensive taste of the region's cuisine.\n\n- **Vegetarian Options:** Karnataka cuisine offers a rich array of vegetarian dishes, so even if you're a pescatarian or vegetarian, you'll find plenty to enjoy.\n\nHubli's culinary scene is sure to enhance your visit with its flavorful and diverse offerings. Enjoy your gastronomic journey!",
  "response_tokens": [
